functionDescription: This function attempts to initialize a Lua tag method by setting a value and calling an associated function.

inputInterfaces.name: i2
inputInterfaces.meaning: An integer value used in the tag method operation

inputInterfaces.name: flip
inputInterfaces.meaning: A flag indicating whether to flip the operation

inputInterfaces.name: event
inputInterfaces.meaning: The event type for the tag method

inoutInterfaces.name: L
inoutInterfaces.meaning: The Lua state in which the operation is performed

inoutInterfaces.name: p1
inoutInterfaces.meaning: A pointer to the first value for the operation

inoutInterfaces.name: res
inoutInterfaces.meaning: The result of the tag method operation
